&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE POSITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The VP of Design and Cost Engineering is responsible for leading the HV Engineering, Development Engineering and Estimating teams, focused on derisking development pipeline and maximizing project value through technical and costing expertise. This role reports to our EVP, Engineering and Construction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-parastyle=&quot;Body&quot;&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS AND RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:200,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role manages and is responsible for team associated with all technical design and costing needs prior to equipment selection and EPC contracting.&amp;nbsp; Expertise is required across HV gen-tie and substation, PV and BESS design and costing. This role is highly cross-functional, and requires management of direct internal team, external engineering consultants and project team activities and peers. It combines depth of technical and commercial knowledge with the ability to drive design and estimating strategy in line with project and business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversees design and cost engineering work across entire pipeline, spanning full development lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support project and site diligence, managing internal resourcing and external consultant strategy for engineering studies and drawing packages pre-EPC contracting in support of internal assessments, or LGIA or permitting processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage and assess projects with different layers of uncertainty, with ability to drive process and tools to accurately assess land, layout and costing considerations with limited information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create engineering related project budgets and 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; party scopes for Engineering studies (hydro, Geotech, etc), and for design work to support LGIA and permitting processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify issues and gaps in processes and analysis, work with key stakeholders to algin towards next steps and solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively communicate deeply technical subject matter considerations, opportunities and risks to project teams, functional leads, and executives in a manner appropriate for audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain in-house estimating tools across all technologies that are dynamic for automation and design and pricing iteration and automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand cash flow considerations related to equipment and EPC contracting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work and coordinate in highly cross-functional manner across key stakeholders (Development, Optimization Engineering, Storage Engineering, Procurement, EPC, and CM)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to identify Value Engineering and project design derisking strategies across full development lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and maintain relationships and strategy for use of 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; party consultants and EPC negotiations and contracting.&lt;/li&gt;
